# Health Insurance Streaming Project

## Project Goal

Build an end-to-end streaming data engineering project using:

* Kafka
* Spark Structured Streaming
* Delta Lake
* Bronze → Silver → Gold Architecture
* RAG Integration (Future Phase)

---

# Step 1 - Create Project Folder

```bash
mkdir health-insurance-streaming
cd health-insurance-streaming
```

---

# Step 2 - Create Docker Compose File

refer to script in the folder 

---

# Step 3 - Start Kafka Environment

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Verify containers:

```bash
docker ps
```

Expected Containers:

```text
zookeeper
kafka
kafka-ui
```

---

# Step 4 - Open Kafka UI

Open:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

Expected Cluster:

```text
local
```

---

# Step 5 - Connect to Kafka Container

```bash
docker exec -it kafka bash
```

---

# Step 6 - List Existing Topics

```bash
kafka-topics \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--list
```

Expected:

```text
__consumer_offsets
```

---

# Step 7 - Create Kafka Topic

```bash
kafka-topics \
--create \
--topic health_claims_topic \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--partitions 1 \
--replication-factor 1
```

Verify:

```bash
kafka-topics \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--list
```

Expected:

```text
__consumer_offsets
health_claims_topic
```

---

# Step 8 - Test Producer

```bash
kafka-console-producer \
--topic health_claims_topic \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092
```

Sample Message:

```json
{"claim_id":"1","amount":1000}
```

---

# Step 9 - Test Consumer

Open another terminal:

```bash
docker exec -it kafka bash
```

Run:

```bash
kafka-console-consumer \
--topic health_claims_topic \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--from-beginning
```

Expected Output:

```json
{"claim_id":"1","amount":1000}
```

---

# Current Architecture

```text
Producer
   |
   v
Kafka Topic (health_claims_topic)
   |
   v
Consumer
```

